         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Easter 1883. ¶  ¶ I have to express my best thanks, dear Sir Charles, for your attentive kindness of sending me the volume of the brilliant orations, delivered by you as Head of the Sydney–University....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.03.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Charles Nicholson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Wisley Library, Royal Horticultural Society, London. </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter tipped into p. iii of the library's copy of B83.03.04. In 1883, Easter fell on 25 March.</p>
               </note>Easter 1883.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to express my best thanks, dear Sir Charles, for your attentive kindness of sending me the volume of the brilliant orations, delivered by you as Head of the Sydney–University.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nicholson (1878?).</p>
               </note> I shall treasure this book as much for the erudite and elegant discourses perpetuated therein, as also on account of the generous feelings, which prompted you in offering this additional Souvenir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Meanwhile you will have received a copy of the Census of Australian plant-species,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.03.04.</p>
               </note> in which at p. 94 you will see entered the <name key="Hoya">Hoya</name>, named in Honor of Lady Nicholson, and at p. 89 your <name key="Goodenia">Goodenia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Hoya">Hoya</name> nicholsoniae,</seg> B66.10.01, p. 159; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Goodenia">Goodenia</name> nicholsonii,</seg> B59.12.01, p. 203, tab. iv. The plants were named, respectively, around the time of Nicholson’s marriage in 1865 and his creation as a Baronet in 1859.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I pleaded in a former letter the cause of Mr Samuel Davenport of Adelaide and of Dr Brownless of Melbourne as among the most deserving of Australians for honors from the British throne.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> As her Majesty’s Birthday is soon approaching again, perhaps their long services for Australia will receive on that occasion the generous consideration of the […].<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One or more lines obscured where final page is tipped into volume.</p>
               </note> I have written on behalf of both to Sir Henry Barkly also.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Brownless was appointed C.M.G. in 1888 and K.C.M.G. on 2 January 1893 (ADB); Davenport was knighted in 1884 and in 1886 appointed K.C.M.G. The letters to Barkly to which M refers have not been found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is stated, that in Sydney Hydrophobia has broke out,<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald,</seg> 24 February 1883, p. 25; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australian medical journal</seg>, 15 March 1883, p. 127.</p>
               </note> of which dreadful disease we had hitherto only in Australia one isolated case at Hobarton.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In 1867. See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australian medical journal, </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol. 12 (1867), pp. 166-84, and Saunders <seg style="font-style: italic; ">et al.</seg> (1995), p. 43.</p>
               </note> It would be a sad calamity, if the condition for that disease had arisen permanently in this part of the Globe now also.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Goodenia">Goodenia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hoya">Hoya</name>
            </p>
         </div>
